"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-what-are-olympic-and-paralympic-medals-made-of-tradition-history-2024-paris-olympics-medals-and-more\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"There is no better feeling than standing on the Olympic podium with a medal draped around your neck while hearing your country's national anthem being played.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 158, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the ultimate symbol of achievement, triumph, and accomplishment-a sign that your name is forever carved in the history of greatness.\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the reason why so many athletes sacrifice their lives, their time, and their bodies in pursuit of Olympic dreams.\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic medals are synonymous with glory.\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 458, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But they were not always the traditional gold, silver, and bronze that we are familiar with today.\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 557, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 1896 Olympic Games in Athens, Greece first-place winners received a silver medal along with an olive branch.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.9947093724533952, \"rank\": 0.005318752888804063, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}, {\"begin\": 596, \"end\": 602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9080940033304417, \"rank\": 0.10115711370386296, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Second and third-place finishers received bronze medals and a laurel branch.\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 751, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The tradition of handing out gold, silver, and bronze medals wasn't introduced until the 1904 Games-8 years later-in St. Louis, Missouri.\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri\", \"score\": 0.9991638157838714, \"rank\": 0.0006579080456557486, \"text\": \"Missouri\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surprisingly, the gold medal only contains about six grams of pure gold which encases the exterior part of the medal.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medals consist mostly of silver, putting them at a value of approximately $750 to $850 dollars (based solely on the value of the materials).\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Silver medals are made out of pure silver, while bronze medals consist of about 95% copper and 5% zinc.\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But all three medals will be getting a special upgrade for the 2024 Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Every 2024 Paris Olympic and Paralympic medal will contain a central 18-gram, hexagonal piece of wrought iron from the monumental Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1484, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The iron was removed and preserved during the 20th-century renovation.\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024  Paris 2024  The hexagonal shape is a tribute to the country's nickname \\\"\\\"L'hexagone\\\" affectionally crafted because the nation is shaped like a hexagon.\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1557, \"end\": 1567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.899236983204795e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1569, \"end\": 1579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.899236983204795e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rear side of the Olympic medals will feature the traditional Olympic rings and Nike-the Greek goddess of victory.\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 1839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1814, \"end\": 1819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.9980799483309373, \"rank\": 0.0013303775476892511, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the back of the Paralympic medals will include the words \\\"Paris\\\" and \\\"2024 written in braille along with the Agitos.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1904, \"end\": 1909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999436658997, \"rank\": 5.633409268284129e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1955, \"end\": 1961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agitos\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_symbols\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024    RELATED:2024 Paris Olympic, Paralympic medals unveiled with Eiffel Tower pieces  A Division ofNBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 2085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2069, \"title\": \"